<p class="p">In a next step, the bivariate distribution of the estimated relative trends is mapped to the global urban land, i.e., grid cells defined as urban [
 <xref rid="pone.0189451.ref014" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">14</xref>]. In so doing, for each corresponding grid cell, the proposed Euclidian distance 
 <inline-formula id="pone.0189451.e005" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <graphic xlink:href="pone.0189451.e005.jpg" id="pone.0189451.e005g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M5" class="math">
    <mover accent="true" class="mover">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">d</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mo class="mo">→</mo>
    </mover>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> is being assessed, with 
 <disp-formula id="pone.0189451.e006" class="disp-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <graphic xlink:href="pone.0189451.e006.jpg" id="pone.0189451.e006g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M6" class="math">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mover accent="true" class="mover">
      <mi class="mi">d</mi>
      <mo class="mo">→</mo>
     </mover>
     <mo class="mo">=</mo>
     <msqrt class="msqrt">
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <msubsup class="msubsup">
        <mi class="mi">d</mi>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mi class="mi">a</mi>
         <mi class="mi">i</mi>
         <mi class="mi">r</mi>
        </mrow>
        <mn class="mn">2</mn>
       </msubsup>
       <mo class="mo">+</mo>
       <msubsup class="msubsup">
        <mi class="mi">d</mi>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mi class="mi">p</mi>
         <mi class="mi">r</mi>
         <mi class="mi">c</mi>
        </mrow>
        <mn class="mn">2</mn>
       </msubsup>
      </mrow>
     </msqrt>
    </mrow>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
  <label class="label">(1)</label>
 </disp-formula> where 
 <italic class="italic">d</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">air</italic>
 </sub> is equal to the estimated relative change in mean annual surface air temperature in the given grid cell, and 
 <italic class="italic">d</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">prc</italic>
 </sub> is equal to the observed relative trend in mean annual total precipitation, respectively. As mentioned earlier, the Euclidian distance 
 <inline-formula id="pone.0189451.e007" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <graphic xlink:href="pone.0189451.e007.jpg" id="pone.0189451.e007g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M7" class="math">
    <mover accent="true" class="mover">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">d</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mo class="mo">→</mo>
    </mover>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> will be the greater the higher 
 <italic class="italic">d</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">air</italic>
 </sub> and/or 
 <italic class="italic">d</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">prc</italic>
 </sub>. It will thus help to identify urban hotspots of climate change.
</p>
